citation: Proclamation under the Fishing (Licence Ownership and Interest) Registration Act 2001 (Tas)
text:
Proclamation under the Fishing (Licence Ownership and Interest) Registration Act 2001

I, the Governor in and over the State of Tasmania and its Dependencies in the Commonwealth of Australia, acting with the advice of the Executive Council, by this my proclamation made under section 2 of the Fishing (Licence Ownership and Interest) Registration Act 2001 fix 1 July 2002 as the day on which that Act commences.

4 June 2002

G. S. M. GREEN

Governor

By His Excellency's Command,

D. E. LLEWELLYN

Minister for Primary Industries, Water and Environment

Displayed and numbered in accordance with the Rules Publication Act 1953.

Notified in the Gazette on 12 June 2002

This proclamation is administered in the Department of Primary Industries, Water and Environment.
